TASK 1 — Kubernetes Deployment

Goal from assignment:

Deploy frontend, backend, database in Kubernetes.

We will convert Docker Compose → Kubernetes manifests.

Step 1 — Install Kubernetes (FREE)

Use Kind (Kubernetes in Docker)

Install:

https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/

Install kubectl:

https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/
Create Cluster
kind create cluster --name dodo-cluster

Check:

kubectl get nodes
Step 2 — Push Your Images to DockerHub

Create free account:

https://hub.docker.com

Login:

docker login

Tag images:

docker tag dodo-app-devops-frontend tripti/dodo-frontend:v1
docker tag dodo-app-devops-backend tripti/dodo-backend:v1

Push:

docker push tripti/dodo-frontend:v1
docker push tripti/dodo-backend:v1

Now Kubernetes can pull them.

Step 3 — Create Kubernetes Project Structure

Inside your repo:

dodo-app-devops
│
├── k8s
│   ├── frontend
│   ├── backend
│   ├── database
│   ├── ingress
│   └── namespace.yaml
Step 4 — Create Namespace

k8s/namespace.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: dodo

Apply:

kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml
Step 5 — Deploy PostgreSQL

k8s/database/postgres-deployment.yaml

This satisfies:

✔ Deployment
✔ Service
✔ Persistent storage (bonus)

Step 6 — Deploy Backend

k8s/backend/deployment.yaml

Includes:

✔ Deployment
✔ Service
✔ ConfigMap
✔ Secrets
✔ health checks

Example readiness probe:

readinessProbe:
  httpGet:
    path: /health
    port: 5000
  initialDelaySeconds: 5
Step 7 — Deploy Frontend

Frontend deployment:

tripti/dodo-frontend:v1

Expose using service.

Step 8 — Ingress Controller

Install nginx ingress:

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/main/deploy/static/provider/kind/deploy.yaml

Create:

k8s/ingress.yaml

Example:

/ → frontend
/api → backend
Step 9 — Horizontal Pod Autoscaler

Assignment requirement.

Example:

kubectl autoscale deployment backend \
  --cpu-percent=50 \
  --min=2 \
  --max=5

This automatically scales backend pods.

Step 10 — Resource Limits

Example:

resources:
  requests:
    memory: "128Mi"
    cpu: "250m"
  limits:
    memory: "512Mi"
    cpu: "500m"

Assignment requirement.

TASK 2 — CI/CD Pipeline

Use GitHub Actions (FREE).

Folder:

.github/workflows

Create:

ci.yml

Pipeline stages:

Push code
   ↓
Lint
   ↓
Build Docker Images
   ↓
Push to DockerHub
   ↓
Deploy to Kubernetes

Example triggers:

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
Add Container Security Scan

Use Trivy (free).

Example step:

trivy image tripti/dodo-backend:v1
GitOps Deployment (Assignment Requirement)

Install ArgoCD

kubectl create namespace argocd

Install:

kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

ArgoCD will deploy your manifests automatically.

TASK 3 — Monitoring & Observability

Install Prometheus + Grafana

Free.

Install Helm:

https://helm.sh

Install monitoring stack:

helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts

Install:

helm install monitoring prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack

You now get:

✔ Prometheus
✔ Grafana
✔ AlertManager

Logging (Free)

Use Loki + Grafana

Install:

helm install loki grafana/loki-stack

Now logs from all containers go to Grafana.

Distributed Tracing

Install Jaeger

kubectl create namespace observability

Deploy Jaeger operator.

Now you get request tracing.

TASK 4 — Security Hardening

Required in assignment.

RBAC

Create roles:

developer
operator
admin

Example:

Role
RoleBinding
ClusterRole
Pod Security

Prevent dangerous containers:

privileged: false
readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
Network Policies

Restrict communication.

Example:

frontend → backend allowed
backend → database allowed
everything else blocked
Container Scanning

Use:

Trivy

Already added in CI pipeline.

Secrets Management

Use Sealed Secrets (free).

This encrypts Kubernetes secrets.

Install:

kubectl apply -f sealed-secrets-controller.yaml
